<br>
<br>
Nearly everyone who says wizards are fine in groups is of the 63+ w/aa crowd.  The original post stated that at that point wizards are fairly balanced.<br>
<br>
A <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>few</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> others think we are OK in the 50's...  But the reality is that while we may scrape by, nearly everyone else contributes more to a group than we do.<br>
<br>
No one cares how efficient we are.  No one cares about cast/recast times--except us.  I have to laugh now that damage is visual, and I actually get asked to burn with Ice Comet...  I use rains for normal group damage, and get lots of Ooooh from the 600, 600, 600...<br>
<br>
I can get groups, it's not terrificaly difficult when it's even possible, but some days it's just not possible.  I've been turned down in a group for a 47 rogue in PoJ, and I'm 53.3 /boggle.<br>
<br>
<br>
Wizards may end up Ok, but the 50-59 game just outright sucks.  Big improvement that would help with perception would be to move some excess spells from 60 a bit lower.  Put a big nuke at 53, another at 57 (perhaps sunstrike and Elnerniks, or slightly smaller new ones) and we will get noticed when we start using them.  <br>
<br>
And I still want an &quot;Ice Bolt of Eci&quot; spell on a pop vendor that is identical except resist to Firebolt of Tallon.  We got a ice bolt at level 1, and 61 is the brave new world. <p><br>
