It's perception, but it's also what a LOT of players got used to from 51-56 in the Kunark days, to the 1-60 days of Velious where wizards were GROSSLY underpowered compared to the melee classes.<br>
<br>
Think about it, we went for a LONG LONG LONG time where wizard damage was considered sub-par.  AA points in Luclin went a long way to helping, but it took until PoP AA abilities for wizards to really get back to being considered a &quot;primary damage dealing class&quot;.  <br>
<br>
In the pre-60 game, I agree, wizards need work, but being able to get to level 65 has done something a lot of people have overlooked.  A lot of the OLD uber encounters are now able to get taken down by the average high level guild.  The perception that wizards as a class don't have the damage output needed to compete in the 60+ range is somewhat flawed.  Focus items, flowing thoughts, horses(ok, only in outdoor zones, but still deserves to be mentioned), these things have all boosted wizard power levels.  Now that all characters can see our damage output(if they don't turn it off), the perceived impact of our spells can at least be correct.  Dropping a 604 damage Conflagration at level 44 is still a decent bit of damage/cast.<br>
  If you want an ID 3 item, it IS possible to buy a Erudite made robe now.  So it's not impossible to get the items needed to boost damage output.  <br>
